$interpreted: : The day of the ceremony...
Jia-Shen: Well, if it ain't Miss Chi~yuki!
Chiyuki: Ah, Mr. Jia-Shen. How are Pang and them doing?
Jia-Shen: Oh, just dandy. Pang's resting it off, the rest of 'em are stuck there watchin' over him and such. They couldn't come with me.
Chiyuki: Ah...
Jia-Shen: Don't you need'ta prepare for hostin' the ceremony and all?
Chiyuki: No, my work is done. I'm simply a guest, now.
Jia-Shen: Over, huh? Well, time sure does fly... Got a new arbiter now and everything.
Chiyuki: You know, there's still a bit of time. Would you like to check out that circus? I think they're rehearsing.
Jia-Shen: Circus, huh? Alright, sounds better than nothin'.
Wolf Chieftain: Listen, when we all make a toast, make sure that maggot gets this glass. I sprinkled Highland Cinnabar in it.
Bribed Alliance Guard: Got it.
Jia-Shen: Highland Cinnabar? Isn't that stuff poison!?
Chiyuki: They're trying to kill Tindoiimu!?
Jia-Shen: This ain't good... We've got to warn her!
Wolf Chieftain: Oh, it's you two.
Jia-Shen: Run!
Turtle Chieftain: Damn, I bet they heard everything! Quick, kill those two!
Wolf Chieftain: You can run but you can't hide...
Chiyuki: I can't believe you'd try and kill our new arbiter!
Wolf Chieftain: Watch your mouth, kid! We're doing a public service... maggot extermination!
Jia-Shen: Listen to yerselves, you've no respect!
Turtle Chieftain: And you're just some worthless, tail-less tortoise...
Jia-Shen: Heh, good thing...
Turtle Chieftain: About to die, and you laugh?
Jia-Shen: Good thing I'm a tortoise, not some no-good cheatin' turtle like you!
Turtle Chieftain: Eeeeeh!? Damn! Get them!
TIngko: It's almost over, Princess. All of this is almost over...
Tindoiimu: ……
TIngko: Are you still thinking about Juan-Yun...? Don't beat yourself up over it, it was all an accident.
Tindoiimu: You really think it was an accident?
TIngko: Princess...
Alliance Guard: Would Tindoiimu please take the stage.
Tindoiimu: ...We'll talk about this later.
TIngko: Okay, I'll wait for you outside.
Tindoiimu: Seems like some people aren't here yet.
Qing-Feng: Yes, some things came up. No matter, we can start first.
Qing-Feng: As is tradition, we will first give you our blessings, then you will stand before the crowd as we pass the ceremonial items onto you.
Qing-Feng: Now, Arbiter Maeok, please lead us in the blessing ritual.
Maeok: Tindoiimu, chosen one of the Holy Dragon, we give you our blessings on this most auspicious of days.
Maeok: Morning dew, cleanse your body. Sorghum wine, cleanse your soul.
Maeok: We hope you will give yourself for the good of this Alliance.
Qing-Feng: Give yourself, protect the Alliance.
Toyokuni: Give yourself, protect the Alliance.
Shun: Give yourself, protect the Alliance...
Maeok: Now, a toast---
Chiyuki: Don't drink that! It's poison!
Maeok: Jia-Shen? Chiyuki? What did you just say?
Chiyuki: Those no-good rotten chieftains said they put Highland Cinnabar in your drink, Tindoiimu! They wanna kill you!
Qing-Feng: ……
Turtle Chieftain: Please excuse their ramblings, they're drunk. We've been trying to escort them off the premises...
Jia-Shen: Nonsense, do we look drunk to you!?
Panther Chieftain: Just like a drunkard to profess his sobriety!
Seahorse Chieftain: Very unbecoming of you, Miss Chiyuki!
Bull Chieftain: You should be ashamed of yourself, making a mockery of our ceremony!
Chiyuki: Please...!
Qing-Feng: Ahem... I understand that you two are guests here at our ceremony, and yet I cannot stand for this blatant disrespect.
Qing-Feng: If you have no proof for your claims, then I advise you both to watch your tongues.
Jia-Shen: Arbiter, I swear we're telling the truth!
Maeok: Ah...
Tindoiimu: Poison, hmm? Let's see...
Tindoiimu: Looks like poison to me.
Qing-Feng: ……
Maeok: Qing-Feng, you really... why!?
Qing-Feng: Why? To save this Alliance, that's why!
Maeok: What?
Qing-Feng: The Insect Tribe has been a stain on our shoes since this Alliance's inception! And now for a maggot to be our arbiter... it's a mockery!
Maeok: And yet she won the tournament fair and square, and we must respect that! It is the will of the Udumbara, have you forgotten!?
Qing-Feng: And yet the will of the Udumbara is something only our people can understand! It doesn't apply to some filthy bug!
Maeok: You...!
Maeok: What are you doing!?
Qing-Feng: No need to scream. I've replaced the guards with my own guys, and we're about to exterminate these bugs once and for all.
Toyokuni: Enough! Is the Holy Dragon a joke to you!?
Toyokuni: This Alliance was born from the Holy Dragon! If you continue down this road, don't expect my tribe to play along!
Qing-Feng: That's if I ever let you get back to them, fool!
Tindoiimu: Qing-Feng... you're hopeless.
Qing-Feng: Read the room, maggot. You're the hopeless one.
Toyokuni: Are you complicit in this too, General Shun? Colluding with villains?
Shun: I...
Qing-Feng: Think of your tribe, General Shun. Think of your animosity with the insects... Why make enemies with us for one bug?
Toyokuni: Shun!
Tindoiimu: Forget it, the Tiger Tribe and Insect Tribe have hated each other since the beginning. He'd never help me.
Toyokuni: I'm disappointed in you, Shun.
Qing-Feng: We're disappointed in you, Toyokuni.
Shun: Gyaaaagh! Everyone just shut up!
Shun: I may not get along with the Insect Tribe, but I'm also a warrior, and if Tindoiimu won fair and square, I'll respect that!
Qing-Feng: Insolent bugs, you'll never stand in my way! All of you will die here today!
Jia-Shen: it's no good, there are too many of them.
Maeok: Don't give up, we...
Tindoiimu: ...Maeok!?
Shun: Arbiter!!
Toyokuni: Oh no, Arbiter!
Qing-Feng: Why would you do something so stupid? Forget it, just kill them all.
Bull Chieftain: Damn, they ran away!
Qing-Feng: Relax, Maeok is hurt, they can't get far. Go after them!
